JOHANNESBURG - Bafana Bafana will begin the defence of their Cosafa Castle Cup with a clash against Tanzania on Sunday at Royal Bafokeng Stadium in Phokeng, near Rustenburg (start 3pm).Tanzania, who came into the tournament as guests at this year s tournament, earned the right to face Bafana Bafana after they topped Group A.READ: Jordaan says these are exciting times for SA footballIn their last group stages match, Tanzania were held to a 1-1 draw by Mauritius, which saw them finish on five points after three fixtures.The East Africans were tied on points with Angola, who drew with Malawi in the other group match played simultaneously, but Tanzania advanced to the last eight due to a better goal difference.READ: Bafana defeats Nigeria 2-0Victory for South Africa against Tanzania will see them face the winners of the Botswana vs Zambia clash on Wednesday, 5 July.Bafana Bafana have won this competition on four occasions 2002, 2007, 2008, 2016 joining Zambia and Zimbabwe as the only three nations to achieve this feat. African News Agency